<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1757" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1757">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 819.77/173.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Price</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-07">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 7, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Consult freely with Colonel Goethals and discuss with him all details of
                            the Hebard railway contract. You should bear in mind that the three
                            points to which the Department objects are (1) contravention of Article
                            5 of the Canal Convention (2) features objectionable from military
                            standpoint (3) pledging annuity of $250,000 or income from six million
                            dollars permanently invested.</p>
                        <p>Report fully, by cable, if necessary, conclusions reached at this
                            conference.</p>
                        <p>Department desires duplicate copies with translations of proposed
                            contract with Hebard and Company. State if this is ad referendum.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>